<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: A common tech forum failing.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2652&amp;p=12857#p12857"><![CDATA[
I agree. The failings are limitations of the phpbb software that this forum uses. I don't think its silly search restrictions can be fixed. <strong>To search the forum, use Google or Bing.</strong><br /><br />&lt;enter search terms&gt; site:classicshell.net/forum<br /><br />e.g.1, if you don't know how to change Start button, <br /><br />In Google or Bing's search box, type: change start button site:classicshell.net/forum <br /><br />e.g. 2 if you want to know how to add some folder, let's say, 'Videos' to the Start menu, search like this:<br /><br />In Google or Bing's search box, type: add videos start menu site:classicshell.net/forum <br /><br />e.g. 3. If you want to search for Taskbar related topics, type: taskbar site:classicshell.net/forum in Google's search box.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Sun May 18, 2014 9:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
